  "text": "In our study of the linear scaling regime, we apply a wide array of methods, starting with the method of moments (which often boils down to path-counting), special functions (orthogonal polynomial) theory and generating functions, as well as one important result from the work of Anderson and Zeitouni [CITATION_1] (more details in Section 4).",
